texts.text: >A woman weeps as she sits in the middle of a room...
*Cry*
>Drawn beneath her is a large magic circle.
This... This should do it...!
>The circle emits a bright flash of light and something begins to appear!
The seal is broken... At long last...
It... It worked...!
Now I can finally...!
But... I am incomplete... You! You have botched the ritual!
What...? Noooo!
>The city has gone quiet with people hunched over on the sidewalk...
All these people look so down and out.
Some of them look exhausted. This doesnâ€™t feel like Akihabara at all.

*Nod*
They need airsoft in their lives.
The thrill of never knowing when you're going to be shot.
It'll wake anyone right up.
No, that's exactly what horror flicks are for.
Experiencing a sort of fear that you never can in real life.
Newbie, which do you think is better?
Airsoft.
Horror movies.
I knew it! I'll lend you my M4 next time then!
It's easy to use even for a novice but also popular among seasoned veterans.
You hold it like this! And adjust your sights like...
Hm? What's that...?
Yes!
I mean, fear takes shape in different ways,
but if you want to experience it in its purest form, then your best bet is
an absolute classic like "Evil Dead".
And it has to be the original by Sam Raimi! Not the remake!
The final scene where you really get to see how fragile humans really are
is one of my favorites. That kind of directing is just pure art.
Speaking of Sam Raimi, his other works include...
Newbie, shall I shut him up for you?
Hold on. I had no plans to get shot.
Newbie, let's have a movie marathon sometime soon!
Wait... Over there...
>Rika spots a person collapsed over in an alley.
Are you alright?!

*Groan*
My body feels so heavy...
There's someone else over there too!
Something's wrong. This domain needs a barrier.
Huh? You mean that thing everyone's been doing lately...?
Yes. Decoherence Field... Expansion!
Oh. Nevermind.
Death... Hate...
A demon's possessing them!
They're saying... "Death" and "hate"...
If you... Die... Friend...!
It's gonna kill that person!
We need to deal with it now! Devil Download!
*Groan*
Are you okay?
Oh, yeah. I feel much better. I guess it was a ghost or something.
Well, close enough. We dealt with the source of the issue.
Uh, okay... I was joking but... Thanks.
This... This looks like a spirit that's turned into a demon.
Wait, does that mean there are more of them around here...?!
We need to hurry and help anyone we can!
Devil Download!
Devil Download!!
Devil Download!!!

*Pant*
I think that's everything.
So many dead spirits... What are they?
We should report back to Megakin at least too.
Aight... So these spirits are turnin' into demons and tryin' to kill people.
It seems so.
They seem to be driven by hate even in death.
Yo, if that's the case there should be way more.
Hate to say it, but lots of folks die clingin' to those sort of thoughts.
1 or 2 is nothin' at all, but somethin' ain't right here.
What do you think is going on?
Hey. How about a pop quiz?
What's the one place where folks are most likely to die?
Umm... High traffic intersections that are poorly designed?
Nah.
Hospitals yo.
Oh, you might be right. Collisions, disease, old age... Everything.
They'll all be sent to a hospital before they die.
Yo, I gotta think these spirits are poppin' up after someone dies.
Any hospitals near where y'all are right now?
I see. Now that you mention it,
these people seem like they collapsed but all point in one direction.
If we head towards that direction... It's Akihabara Hospital...
That might be the actual source of this.
Yo, if y'all figure out where the source is, it might be possible to stop this.
Rika, Shiang Sun and Newbie. It's up to y'all to investigate this.
Copy.
Aight, I'm countin' on ya!
Well, we're here. Akihabara Hospital's patient ward.
There!
*Groan*
Most of the patients are being attacked.
Wait! Over there too!
*Scream*
That one can see these things? And the thing right next to him...
It's alright. Just stay behind me.
B-but! I can't let you be my shield, Gemori...!
>The boy in the patient gown jumps out in front of the demon.
Hate... HATE!
Watch out!
Let's go. One shot is all I need!
